<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/9803> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #9803" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cichorius identifies him as a Tribune of the Soldiers based on the list of members of the staff of Pompeius Strabo at Asculum (ILS 8888; RS 144-155)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/9058> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #9058" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/7> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "p. 744, footnote 203" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7194> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7194" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cos. 81. Procos. in Macedonia. See MRR 2.74, 80, 84, 86, 89. An inscription of Thasos (Dunant and Pouilloux, Etudes Thas. 5.2, no. 175), which follows immediately after an SC and letter of Sulla (no. 174) confirming rights and privileges he has granted, identifies the proconsul named in it as the consul of 81 and proconsul of Macedonia from 80 to 77, and supplies the filiation missing in Fast. Cap. See Badian, PBSR 33, 1965, 48-51, with a stemma of the family. After his return and triumph he was prosecuted unsuccessfully by Julius Caesar (MRR 2.89).\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7175> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7175" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cos. 72. Sumner presents a good case for identifying the Cn. Cornelius Cn. f. Pal. in Pompeius Strabo's consilium at Asculum with the consul of 72 (Orators 124-126; Shackleton Bailey, Studies 112-113). The filiation given above assumes that he was an adoptive son of Cn. Cornelius Lentulus (178). Cos. 97. See Sumner and Shackleton Bailey, above, and also Criniti, L'Epigrafe di Asculum 108-110; who favors Cn. Cornelius Dolabella (135), Pr. urb. 81. Monetalis: Cn. (Cornelius) (Cn. f.) Lentul(us) (Clodianus). Add in MRR 2.437, and refer to Crawford, RRC 1.356-357, no. 345, 88? B.C.\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4318> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4318" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Proconsul in Macedonia (see 80-78, Promagistrates). He returned, probably in this year, to celebrate his triumph (Cic. Pis. 44; Suet. Iul. 4.1; see Degrassi 564). He was prosecuted for extortion by Julius Caesar, but acquitted (Cic. Brut. 317; Voll. 2.43.3; Val. Max. 8.9.3; Ascon. 26, and 74C; Plut. Caes. 4.1; Tac. Dial. 34, misdated; Suet. Iul. 4.1; of. Quintil. Inst. Or. 12.6.1, and 7.4; Malcovati, FOR 3.108; and confused statements in Auct. Vir. Ill. 78.2; and Ps.-Ascon. 194, and 234 Stangl)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4317> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4317" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "5 See note 4." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4292> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4292" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Presumably continued as Proconsul in Macedonia until succeeded by Ap. Claudius in 77 (see above, on Ap. Claudius, and 80-79, Promagistrates)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4268> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4268" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Governor of Macedonia. See 80, and 78, Promagistrates.\"/>" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4241> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4241" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Governor, probably Proconsul, of Macedonia. See 79, and 78, Promagistrates." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4193> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4193" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cic. Leg. Agr. 2.35; Fast. Cap., Degrassi 54f., 130, 484f. (Tullius' name entire; Cn. Q ------ ]); App. BC 1.100; Gell. 15.28.3; Chr. 354 (Decola et Dolabella); Fast. Hyd. (Diecula et Dolabella); Chr. Pasc. # Cassiod." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4174> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4174" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "His title or titles not preserved. He held command of a fleet under Sulla (Plut. Comp. Lysand. and Sull. 2.4), and served at Sacriportus and at the Colline Gate (Plut. Sull. 28.4; 29.4)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4133> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4133" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Held command of a fleet under Sulla (Plut. Comp. Lys. and Sulla 2.4)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3923> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3923" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "11 The cognomen might also be Blasio or Lentulus. Cichorius favors Dolabella beeause the later careers of the known Dolabellas parallel so closely that of Lepidus." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/10034> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #10034" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/31> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Triumph ex Macedonia. MRR II.89, Itgenshorst no. 247 (78?), Rich. no. 247 (77)." .
